text.section:
In this section, "child dependent of the domestic partner" means an individual who:
is:
the natural child, stepchild, adopted child, or grandchild of the domestic partner of an insured;
a child placed with the domestic partner of an insured for legal adoption; or
a child who is under testamentary or court appointed guardianship, other than temporary guardianship of less than 12 months' duration, of the domestic partner of an insured;
is a dependent, as that term is used in 26 U.S.C. §§ 104, 105, and 106, and any regulations adopted under those sections, of the domestic partner of an insured;
resides with the insured;
is unmarried; and
is under the age of 25 years.
